boone.io

Class CSVPatternFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • boone.io.IOFilter
      • boone.io.CSVPatternFilter

  • public class CSVPatternFilter
extends IOFilter
    The CSV pattern filter assumes that a complete pattern (input and target) is written in a single line (a record), where the values are separated by a specific character (default is the comma ','). First there are 'inputCount' input values and then 'targetCount' target values. There may be an optional header, which is a single line at the beginning of the file, where the pattern features may be given a name. If there, the header is ignored. Optional comment lines must start with a '#' character (these lines are also ignored). Blank lines are ignored, too.
    Since:
    September 27, 2011
    Version:

    Author:
    Helmut A. Mayer
